  "original_title": "\u0dc4\u0daf\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0dd2 \u0db1\u0dd3\u0dad\u0dd2 \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dcf\u0daf\u0dba \u0dc4\u0dd9\u0da7",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Emergency legislation debate tomorrow",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The debate on the emergency law will be held in Parliament all day tomorrow (27).",
        "The debate will be held today from 10:00 am to 4:30 pm and the declaration of emergency laws will be adopted this afternoon after the debate.",
        "Parliament will meet tomorrow (27) at 10.00 am under the chairmanship of Speaker Mahinda Yapa Abeywardena.",
        "This Emergency Declaration was issued under the Public Safety Act when the current President was the Acting President.",
        "The then Acting President made this emergency declaration in the Special Gazette No. 2288/30 dated July 17, 2022. According to the legal provisions, the declaration of emergency will lapse if the approval of the Parliament is not obtained within 14 days.",
        "It is stated in the Gazette that this announcement has been issued in accordance with the powers of the President of the Public Security Ordinance to ensure public safety and the survival of the country and to maintain essential supplies and services for public life due to the existence of a state of public emergency in Sri Lanka."
      ],
